<p><b>Why is a business foundation important?</b> When starting a company, its important to have a strong foundation. This means having a clear idea of your business model, your target market, your value proposition, your competitive landscape, and your team. If you don't have a clear foundation, your company will likely struggle to get off the ground.</p>
